The paper deals with the computational complexity of problems related to discrete Morse theory, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG) and combinatorial topology (cs.DM). The paper also discusses algorithms for computing optimal Morse matchings on triangulations of 3-manifolds, which falls under the category of computational discrete structures (cs.DS) and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper discusses the topological significance of the chosen parameters, which is related to computational complexity theory (cs.CC).
